&lt;p&gt;Band 7 Ward Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Heart Assessment Centre (HAC), Hammersmith Hospital.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ward Manager (Full Time)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Cardiac Directorate at Imperial College Health Care NHS Trust (ICHT) is seeking an experienced Cardiology nurse to lead its Heart Assessment Centre (HAC) based at Hammersmith Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Imperial has 5 cardiac catheter laboratories and has a 24/7 PPCI service. 3 interventional labs that treat patients undergoing elective angiography, heart failure, complex stenting, rotablation, transcatheter valve implantation (TAVI). In addition to 2 dedicated electro physiology laboratories where patients undergo cardiac resynchronisation (CRT) device implantation and ablations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;___________________________________________________________________&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 7 Ward Manager (Clinical Senior Sister/Charge Nurse)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Heart Assessment Centre (HAC) at Hammersmith Hospital is the front door for Cardiology at ICHT through the delivery of a 24/7 Primary PCI and arrhythmia service covering North West London. The unit has 3 assessment trolleys (1 resus bay) and 9 in-patient beds.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a rare opportunity to combine your clinical cardiology &amp; ECG expertise with management and support the current changing landscape of patient and staff pathways. You should possess a strong background in acute cardiology with 3 years recent cardiology/CCU/HAC experience at Band 6/7 to support this.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be a caring highly motivated individual who demonstrates strong leadership qualities that support collaborative team working across all professional groups, day-case unit, CCU and a stepdown ward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible for the units KPI’s, safe staffing levels and staff education to ensure high quality care is delivered from admission to discharge. The current pandemic has recently changed our pathways and flexibility in adapting to these is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be required to adapt to and manage change effectively and support the delivery of our quality agenda. This post holder will work in both a clinical and managerial capacity and will be supported by a highly visible Matron. This is an excellent opportunity to develop your leadership skills and lead a committed team in a demanding, unpredictable, yet rewarding clinical setting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We believe in developing effective leaders and opportunities exist within the Cardiac Directorate to further support this from both internal supervision and external course opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Expected hours of work are Monday to Friday. Informal visits are strongly encouraged. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Previous applicants need not apply.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer a flexible approach to working hours to meet the needs of the individual and the service. Please talk to us at interview about the flexibility you may need.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details/informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sarah Storey – Matron: sarah.storey1@nhs.net Bleep: 3277 ext: 33403&lt;/p&gt;
